content:
Assets represent the specific products your customers have purchased. Use assets to store information about your customers' products. Assets have a serial number, purchase date, and other related information. They can represent competitor products or versions of your products.

You can create asset hierarchies to represent products with multiple components. View a tree grid of an asset's hierarchy on its detail page. Assets can be linked to cases, work orders, maintenance plans, entitlements, and contract line items.

Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.
title: Setting Up Assets in Service Cloud
